This solution defines a helper function `is_prime` to check if a number is prime. It then iterates through the range from `left` to `right`, collecting all prime numbers in a list. If there are fewer than two prime numbers in this range, it returns `[-1, -1]`. Otherwise, it finds the pair of prime numbers with the smallest difference and returns it.
